'''公共政策民調基金會'''（{{lang-en|Public Policy Polling}}，簡稱'''PPP'''）是一間[[美國|美國]][[民主黨_(美國)|民主黨]]的[[輿論調查|民意調查]]公司<ref name=jensen>{{cite web | language=en | url=http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/main/2008/11/ppps-bias.html | title=PPP's 'Bias' | publisher=Public Policy Polling | date=2008-11-05 | accessdate=2016-10-05 | author=Jensen, Tom | archive-date=2016-10-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010164449/http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/main/2008/11/ppps-bias.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，總部位於[[北卡羅萊納州|北卡羅萊納州]][[羅里_(北卡羅來納州)|羅里]]<ref name=sarlin>{{cite web | language=en | url=http://talkingpointsmemo.com/dc/how-ppp-became-the-it-democratic-pollster | title=How PPP Became The 'It' Democratic Pollster | work={{link-en|Talking Points Memo|Talking Points Memo}} | date=2011-08-22 | accessdate=2016-10-05 | author=Sarlin, Benjy | archive-date=2016-10-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005202552/http://talkingpointsmemo.com/dc/how-ppp-became-the-it-democratic-pollster | dead-url=no }}</ref>。該公司成立於2001年，現任[[總裁|總裁]]兼[[首席执行官|執行長]]是Dean Debnam<ref>[http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/aboutppp/about-us-bios.html "About Us"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/aboutppp/about-us-bios.html |date=20121122071434 }}, ''Public Policy Polling'', 2012. Retrieved on 6 December 2012.</ref>。

除了政治問題，公司還向美國民眾詢問各式各樣的意見，例如上帝<ref>{{cite web |language=en |url=http://www.newsmax.com/InsideCover/God-approval-poll-creator/2011/07/24/id/404610 |title=Public Policy Poll: God Commands 52% Approval |publisher=Newsmax.com |date=2011-07-24 |accessdate=2011-10-21 |archive-date=2011-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105232437/http://www.newsmax.com/InsideCover/God-approval-poll-creator/2011/07/24/id/404610 |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[新世界秩序|新世界秩序]]陰謀論<ref name="Synchronicity Key">{{cite book|language = en|last1=Wilcock|first1=David|title=The Synchronicity Key:the hidden intelligence guiding the universe and you|date=2014-05-29|publisher=橡實文化|isbn=978-9866362880|pages=第69頁}}</ref>、[[全球暖化|全球暖化]]是否為騙局<ref>{{cite web|language=en|url=http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/main/2013/04/conspiracy-theory-poll-results-.html|title=Conspiracy Theory Poll Results|publisher=公共政策民調基金會|date=2013-04-02|accessdate=2017-04-03|archive-date=2017-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930093655/http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/main/2013/04/conspiracy-theory-poll-results-.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[巴拉克·歐巴馬|巴拉克·歐巴馬]]有無上天堂的資格<ref>{{cite web |language=en |last=Rosenbaum |first=Ron |url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/weigel/2011/07/19/only_19_percent_of_republicans_think_obama_would_be_raptured.html |title=Only 19 Percent of Republicans Think Obama Would Be Raptured |publisher=Slate |date=2011-07-19 |accessdate=2011-10-21 |archive-date=2011-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020101401/http://www.slate.com/blogs/weigel/2011/07/19/only_19_percent_of_republicans_think_obama_would_be_raptured.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、是否應該對時尚人士特別徵稅<ref>{{cite web |language=en |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/13/hipster-tax_n_3268094.html |title=Hipster Tax For Being 'So Annoying' Backed By 27 Percent Of Americans: Poll |publisher=The Huffington Post |date=2013-05-13 |accessdate=2013-05-14 |archive-date=2013-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513210409/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/13/hipster-tax_n_3268094.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，以及[[泰德·克魯茲|泰德·克魯茲]]是否是[[黃道十二宮殺手|黃道十二宮殺手]]<ref>{{cite news|language=en|last1=Stuart|first1=Tessa|title=Is Ted Cruz the Zodiac Killer? Maybe, Say 38 Percent of Florida Voters|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/politics/news/is-ted-cruz-the-zodiac-killer-maybe-say-38-percent-of-florida-voters-20160226|accessdate=2016-05-01|work=[[滾石_(雜誌)|滾石 (雜誌)]]|date=2016-02-26|archive-date=2017-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230060210/https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/news/is-ted-cruz-the-zodiac-killer-maybe-say-38-percent-of-florida-voters-20160226|dead-url=no}}</ref>。該公司的調查方式為[[互動式語音應答|互動式語音應答]]以及自動化的[[問卷調查|問卷調查]]<ref name=wsjournal>{{cite news | language=en | url=https://online.wsj.com/article/SB122592455567202805.html | title=Polls Foresaw Future, Which Looks Tough for Polling | last=Bialik | first=Carl | date=2008-11-06 | work=[[華爾街日報|華爾街日報]] | pages=A16 | accessdate=2012-03-12 | archive-date=2013-09-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130916055718/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB122592455567202805.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

